@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ==========================================
### Badge Upload — CARBON_INVENTORY_CALCULATION
### ==========================================

### Step 1: Request Upload URL
# @name requestUploadCarbonInventoryCalculation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/badge/CARBON_INVENTORY_CALCULATION/request-upload HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "originalName": "badge.svg",
    "mimeType": "image/svg+xml"
}


### Step 2: Upload badge to the presigned URL
### NOTE: When STORAGE_PROVIDER=azure_blob_storage, the response also includes
###   uploadHeaders={"x-ms-blob-type":"BlockBlob"} and uploadMethod=PUT.
### When STORAGE_PROVIDER=minio, uploadHeaders is empty and uploadMethod=PUT.
### The .rest format cannot read response headers/method dynamically, so the
### values below assume Azure. For MinIO, drop the x-ms-blob-type line.
PUT {{requestUploadCarbonInventoryCalculation.response.body.uploadUrl}} HTTP/1.1
x-ms-blob-type: BlockBlob
Content-Type: image/svg+xml

< ./test-files/badge.svg


### Step 3: Confirm Upload
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/badge/CARBON_INVENTORY_CALCULATION/confirm-upload HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "uuid": "{{requestUploadCarbonInventoryCalculation.response.body.uuid}}",
    "originalName": "badge.svg"
}


